hiatus hernia is a significant risk factor for gastro-oesophageal reflux disease. It disrupts the normal anatomical barrier at the gastro-oesophageal junction, compromising the lower oesophageal sphincter function and promoting reflux of gastric contents. Apart from this well recognised cause, there are a number of other factors which could contribute to the development of gastro-oesophageal reflux disease (GORD).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAsian ethnicity\u003C/strong\u003E is associated with a lower prevalence of GORD compared to Western populations, likely due to genetic and dietary factors. If anything, infection with \u003Cstrong\u003EHelicobacter pylori \u003C/strong\u003Ewould reduce the risk, as the organism interferes with parietal cell function and reduces the stomach\u0027s ability to produce acid.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThere does not appear to be any difference between the \u003Cstrong\u003Egenders\u003C/strong\u003E with regards to the prevalence of GORD. Whilst smoking and \u003Cstrong\u003Ealcohol \u003C/strong\u003Ecan exacerbate GORD, there is no clear evidence that alcohol promotes its development.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAs with an increasing number of other diseases, \u003Cstrong\u003Eobesity\u003C/strong\u003E is now a well recognised risk factor for the development of GORD.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Hiatus hernia is a significant risk factor for gastro-oesophageal reflux disease by disrupting the normal anatomical barrier at the gastro-oesophageal junction","Asian ethnicity is associated with a lower risk of gastro-oesophageal reflux disease compared to Western populations","Lifestyle and anatomical factors play key roles in the pathogenesis of reflux disease"],"references":["Eusebi LH, Ratnakumaran R, Yuan Y, et al. Global prevalence of, and risk factors for, gastro-oesophageal reflux symptoms: a meta-analysis. Gut 2018; 67:430\u201340","Tack J, Pandolfino JE. Pathophysiology of Gastroesophageal Reflux Disease. Gastroenterology. 2018 Jan;154(2):277-288. doi: 10.1053/j.gastro.2017.09.047. Epub 2017 Oct 14. PMID: 29037470","Herregods TV, Bredenoord AJ, Smout AJ. Pathophysiology of gastroesophageal reflux disease: new understanding in a new era. Neurogastroenterol Motil. 2015 Sep;27(9):1202-13. doi: 10.1111/nmo.12611. Epub 2015 Jun 5. PMID: 26053301","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51372"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15124"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51372","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51372"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-27T15:44:40+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-27T15:44:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7812"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65926"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":""